## Create the Robots.txt File

This tells Google it is allowed to crawl everything.

**1.** Click **"Add file"** → **"Create new file"**

**2.** In filename box type:
```
public/robots.txt
```

**3.** Paste this in content area:
```
User-agent: *
Allow: /
Sitemap: https://docsfactory.in/sitemap.xml
```

**4.** Click green **"Commit changes"**

---

## Submit Sitemap to Google

Wait 2 minutes for Netlify to redeploy, then:

**1.** Go to Google Search Console
```
https://search.google.com/search-console
```

**2.** In the left sidebar click **"Sitemaps"**

**3.** In the box that says "Add a new sitemap" type:
```
sitemap.xml
